            <p>The <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/xbox-games-showcase-june-2025-livestream-and-blog">Xbox Showcase 2025</a> has just concluded, and with it a bunch of new reveals and updates for existing Xbox games have just been thrown out for your viewing pleasure. It was a hefty show, with plenty to look over, marking a lot to look out for those Xbox fans out there.
</p>
<p>Below, we've covered all the major announcements during the Xbox Showcase, with trailers included alongside every game we saw, so consider this your one-stop-shop for everything we saw during the event! In addition, if you want more info on a particular reveal, we'll link to the dedicated news article within the appropriate section.
</p>
<h3>The Outer Worlds 2</h3>
<p>And we're off! First up is <a data-keyword="true" href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/the-outer-worlds">The Outer Worlds</a> 2, which got a new gameplay trailer at the very start of the Xbox Games Showcase. In it, we saw a variety of new locations, rifts that are threatening the colonies, and plenty of anti-capitalist commentary as you'd expect. Plus, plenty of first person shooter action with new weapons and enemies on display. A chunky trailer for a much-anticipated upcoming game.</p>
<p>The Outer Worlds 2 is coming out October 29 2025 on Xbox Series X|S, PC, PS5
